# GOV.UK Frontend interactivity via app JS overrides

Enhance GOV.UK Frontend behaviour **only** in this app’s JavaScript — do not fork or patch vendor GOV.UK Frontend JS.

- Use the packaged GOV.UK Frontend JS as shipped (`govuk-frontend.min.js` / `window.GOVUKFrontend.initAll()` in layout)
- Do **not** edit files under `node_modules/govuk-frontend` or vendor-copied GOV.UK Frontend scripts
- Do **not** reimplement GOV.UK components’ built-in JS in templates or by replacing `initAll()` with custom component initialisers
- App-specific interactivity (extra listeners, journey helpers, show/hide of **macro-rendered** markup, analytics hooks) belongs in `src/frontend/js/` (for example `main.js` and modules it loads)
- Prefer attaching behaviour after official init: enhance existing DOM, do not rebuild GOV.UK component HTML in JS when a macro can render it
- If GOV.UK Frontend JS must change for a bug/upgrade, bump the `govuk-frontend` package — do not paper over it with a vendored fork
